snippet.textDisplay:
Always interesting to hear such love songs.
 
They summarize the selfish understanding of divine in tamasik ideologies quite well - impatience in love but without purity and generosity of spirit of wanting to see one's lover safe and healthy, nonetheless. What remains is only the entitlement of so-called 'belongingness' that suffocates the object of love. 

Ehoje vichar wale kiwe judaiyaan di sardari nu rokange?
Ram kare jehdi gaaliyan tusi priyatam nu dende ho oh twanu vi lag jaawe.
